    <h2>Learn about Family and Friends</h2>
    <p>In this unit, we will learn about family members, friends, and how to describe relationships and people in English. You will also learn some useful phrases to talk about your family and friends.</p>

    <h3 class="section-title">Key Vocabulary</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Mother</strong> - The female parent.</li>
      <li><strong>Father</strong> - The male parent.</li>
      <li><strong>Brother</strong> - A male sibling.</li>
      <li><strong>Sister</strong> - A female sibling.</li>
      <li><strong>Grandmother</strong> - Your mother's or father's mother.</li>
      <li><strong>Grandfather</strong> - Your mother's or father's father.</li>
      <li><strong>Uncle</strong> - Your brother or sister's husband.</li>
      <li><strong>Aunt</strong> - Your brother or sister's wife.</li>
      <li><strong>Cousin</strong> - A child of your uncle or aunt.</li>
      <li><strong>Friend</strong> - A person you know well and like to spend time with.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="section-title">Common Phrases</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>How many brothers and sisters do you have?</strong> - A question to ask about someone's siblings.</li>
      <li><strong>I have one brother and two sisters.</strong> - A way to answer how many siblings you have.</li>
      <li><strong>What does your father do?</strong> - A question about someone's father's occupation.</li>
      <li><strong>My mother is a teacher.</strong> - A way to describe someone's occupation.</li>
      <li><strong>Are you close to your family?</strong> - Asking if someone has a good relationship with their family.</li>
      <strong>Yes, I am very close to my family.</strong> - Responding affirmatively.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="section-title">Grammar Focus: The Possessive 's</h3>
    <p>We use the possessive 's to show that something belongs to someone. For example:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>This is my sister's book.</strong> - The book belongs to my sister.</li>
      <li><strong>That is my father's car.</strong> - The car belongs to my father.</li>
      <li><strong>Is this your friend's pencil?</strong> - Asking if the pencil belongs to your friend.</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="grammar-section">
      <h3 class="section-title">Family Tree Example</h3>
      <p>Here’s an example of a family tree:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Grandparents:</strong> Grandfather and Grandmother</li>
        <li><strong>Parents:</strong> Father and Mother</li>
        <li><strong>Siblings:</strong> Brother and Sister</li>
        <li><strong>Cousins:</strong> Your aunt's or uncle's children</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Family members are connected in many ways. Knowing these words will help you describe your family in English.</p>
